    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a concentrated offensive core, anchored by **Luis Robert Jr.**, who represents our highest efficiency play at a 73.74. Facing Eduardo Rodriguez, **Luis Robert Jr.** gains a massive 14% boost from his dynamic platoon split, allowing him to exploit the lefty-righty advantage in what is projected to be our most productive lineup slot. **Jacob Wilson** also provides a high floor at 64.54; as our leadoff hitter, he capitalizes on a strong spot against Ryan Weathers, with a 10% premium applied for his top-of-the-order positioning. While we are still waiting on official lineups for **Miguel Vargas**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Jackson Merrill**, their respective projections remain in the \"Strong\" 60+ tier, bolstered by favorable matchups against starters with xERAs north of 3.60.\n\nThe most difficult personnel decision of the day involves **Liam Hicks**, who finished with a 38.51 score. While his platoon edge against Lowder (R) provided a significant 11% boost, he ultimately failed to clear our 40.0 \"Zebras\" floor threshold. The primary catalyst for his benching was the elite-level arm of Lowder (2.76 xERA), which effectively neutralized any potential output he might have provided. We are maintaining a disciplined approach with our game caps, choosing to keep **Liam Hicks** on the bench rather than chasing a marginal start. With **Gunnar Henderson**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages** all observing team off-days, our active roster is lean but optimized for daily efficiency. We are monitoring the pending lineups for **Miguel Vargas**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Jackson Merrill** closely; any deviation from their projected #3 spots could necessitate a recalibration of our expected run production against their respective opponents.",
